data.name: richTextBox1.Text
data.value:
Rules
To win you must have a card value as close to 21 as possible, but any card value higher will mean you have lost and the dealer wins. This is called a BUST.
Here the player has a card value of 7.

data.name: richTextBox2.Text
data.value:
The player has two main moves they can take: either HIT or STAND.
A HIT means the player requests another card from the dealer, therefore increasing their card value. However each additional card the player takes, risks them going bust.
A STAND means the player sticks with their current hand, when the risk of taking a new card is too high. However doing this too early will make the chances of winning slim, unless the dealer has a bad hand.
